  "title": "Property Conveyancing Legal Counsel | Junior Lawyer",
  "description": "<ul><li><strong>Position title: Junior Conveyancing Lawyer | Legal Counsel</strong></li><li>Working Days: 5 days</li><li>Working Timing: 9:00 am to 6:00 pm</li><li>Working Location: Telok Ayer</li><li>Starting Salary: $5,500 - $7,000</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications and Requirements:</strong></p><ol><li><p>Bachelor's Degree in Law </p></li><li><p><u><strong>1-3 years of Post-Qualification Experience (PQE) in conveyancing or related legal work.</strong></u></p></li><li><p><u><strong>Familiarity with property laws and conveyancing procedures.</strong></u></p></li></ol><p><strong>Key Responsibilities & Duties:</strong></p><ul><li><p>Prepare and review legal documents related to property transactions. These documents include sale and purchase agreements and loan agreements.</p></li><li><p>You will provide advice to clients on all aspects of buying or selling property. This includes legal issues, financial considerations, and contract matters.</p></li><li><p>Engage in negotiations with the other party’s lawyer for the Option to Purchase (OTP). Provide advice to clients on the conveyancing process and their rights and obligations.</p></li><li><p>Liaise with various parties involved in the transaction, including real estate agents, mortgage lenders, and other relevant stakeholders.</p></li></ul><p><u><strong></strong></u><br /><br />#SCR-carson-cheong<br /></p><p><p>⭕ Cheong Kar Chun ⭕ Team Manager ⭕ R1980386</p><p>⭕ The Supreme HR Advisory ⭕ 14C7279</p><p></p></p>",
